Popular comic skit maker Mr Macaroni has urged fans and social media followers to desist from asking when he will tie the nuptial knots. Mr Macaroni responded to those querying his relationship status in a recent tweet.   House of Reps votes March 3 on constitutional amendment     Akwa Ibom Gov sacks Chief of Staff     National anthem co-author Prof Ogunnaike dies   “Stop asking when I’ll get married. It’s not your business,” he tweeted with finality. Mr Macaroni became popular for his comedy skits where he plays the role of a randy elderly man.